      "message": "I\u0027m not really sure how to refer to a specific font. The backend font API is in firmware/export/font.h. I assume the font numbers ultimately come from font_load().\n\nIt _does_ seem like the font loading code is smart enough to re-use fonts that are already loaded in memory. So it may be reasonable to allow using a font different from the main UI font. If they happen to be identical then there would be no extra memory usage.\n\nIt may be enough to just allow choosing between FONT_SYSFIXED (what is currently used for the keyboard) and the UI font. Maybe with a fallback to FONT_SYSFIXED in case the UI font is so ridiculously huge it would make the keyboard unusable.",
